@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}
<div class="content">
    <div class="jumbotron">
        <p class="lead">
            The Windows Web App Gallery provides simple ways for users to explore, discover, install and deploy your web applications on the Windows platform. Share your web app with millions of Windows users worldwide. Users have a great place to go to discover and install the web apps they want as well as share and learn from user ratings and reviews.
            <a href="http://learn.iis.net/page.aspx/606/microsoft-web-application-gallery-overview/"><span class="label label-primary">Technical overview of how it works</span></a>
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="for-developer-panel">
        <img alt="For Developers" src="/content/images/header-developer.png">
        <p>Users have a great place to go to discover and install the web apps they want as well as share and learn from user ratings and reviews. Hosters now have a simple way to offer and deploy the best free web applications to their customers. And developers get a easy way to distribute their latest apps.Get going with best practices, guidelines and requirements for the Web App Gallery. Once you’re all set, submit your app and we’ll take it from there.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-panel">
        <div class="step1-panel">
            <h3>Adhere to the gallery principles</h3>
            <img src="/content/images/step1-hero.png" alt="Adhere to the gallery principles" />
            <p>First, you need to determine if your web app meets the <a href="http://learn.iis.net/page.aspx/605/web-application-gallery-principles/" title="Windows Web App Gallery Principles">Windows Web App Gallery Principles</a>. Your web app will need to adhere to a few basic criterias for a quality user experience in the Gallery, such as support for the same Windows platforms as the Web PI and no harm to the user’s computer.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="step2-panel">
            <h3>Add support to your app package</h3>
            <img src="/content/images/step2-hero.png" alt="Add support to your app package" />
            <p>Now you need to add support to your ZIP package for Web App Gallery so that we can simplify the installation of your app on Windows. This requires you to add 2 simple XML files to your application zip package. Read the <a href="http://learn.iis.net/page.aspx/578/application-packaging-guide-for-the-windows-web-application-gallery/" title="Web Application Packaging Guidelines" onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank', ''); return false;" onkeypress="window.open(this.href, '_blank', ''); return false;">Windows Web App Packaging Guidelines</a> for a detailed walkthrough.</p>
            <p><span class="important-note">Important! We cannot accept your submission until you've completed this step.</span> For help with packaging your web app, visit the <a href="http://forums.iis.net/1159.aspx" title="Developer Support Forum">Developers Forum</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="step3-panel">
            <h3>Submit your app</h3>
            <img src="/content/images/step3-hero.png" alt="Submit your app" />
            <p>Once you've determined that your web app meets the gallery's principles and you've created a compatible app package, you can now submit your web app using our online form.</p>
            <a href='@Url.RouteUrl(SiteRouteNames.Portal)' title="submit your web app"><img src="/content/images/submit-webapp-btn.png" alt="submit web app" /></a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@section Styles {
    @Styles.Render("~/css/home-index")
}